            . I am a shopman to 
               <persName id="t18310630-285-person2048">
                  Henry 
                  Hart
               <interp inst="t18310630-285-person2048" type="surname" value="Hart"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-285-person2048" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-285-person2048" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who <rs id="t18310630-285-viclabel1495" type="occupation">keeps a clothes-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-285-victim2046 t18310630-285-viclabel1495"></join>. On the 14th of May the prisoner and a man, who called himself his father, came to the shop - I had seen the prisoner on board ship before; they asked Hart to trust them with a pair of shoes and stockings- he took down the father's address, and during that time the prisoner went away with the stockings and shoes; I then missed a jacket and another pair of stockings, which were not sold - the prisoner came back; I said, "You have stolen a jacket;" he said he had not - I afterwards found the prisoner at the station-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-285-person2049">
                  EDWARD 
                  STERN
               <interp inst="t18310630-285-person2049" type="surname" value="STERN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-285-person2049" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-285-person2049" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shopman to Mr. Hart. I stood at the door, and after he had served the prisoner I saw him - go out with the jacket under his arm, but did not know it was stolen - he returned in ten minutes; I said,"Why did you not bring the jacket back which I saw under your arm?" he denied it - I said, "Who did you give the shoes and stockings to?" he said, to his brother; I found his brother with the jacket.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
